Changelog- Easy Event Hire
Week 1 (20-26 April) - I planned the website structure and selected my Easy Event Hire Business concept.i also created basic pages like Home, About, Contact, and Enquiry) and also set up the Navigation Menu.
Week 2 (27 April-3 May) - I added my website content including information about the company, services, images, and Event hire details. i also improved the page organization and content layout.
Week 3 (3-10 May)- I created an external CSS stylesheet and applied styling to all my pages.i also improved with colours like blue, fonts,spacing, and overall visual appearance.
Week 4 (11-17 May)- I enhanced my website layout and user interface. i also added branding elements, footer information, and improved consistency to my pages.
Week 5 (18-24 May) - I also Developed Contact and Enquiry forms using HTML.Tested form structure and ensured all required fields were included.
Week 6 (25-31 May) -I implemented SEO Improvements by adding my pages titles, headings, image alt text, and responsive design features for the mobile devices.
Week 7 (1-7 June) - I created JavaScript folder and file to implement form validation. Added checks for empty fields and incorrect user input.
Week 8 (8-14 June) - Enhanced JavaScript functionality and improved user interaction. Tested Validation rules and corrected erros identified during testing.
Week 9 (15-19 June) - I intergrated EmailJs with the Contact and Enquiry forms using the Service ID, Template ID, and Public Key. Tested email delivery functionality and resloved integration issues.
Week 10( Submission Week)- conducted final testing of navigation, responsiveness, forms, and email functionality.Fixed remaining bugs, prepared project documentation, and deployed the website to a hosting platform for the submission.




